55+ spells</span><hr size=1> The difference is items <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> define</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> melee classes whereas for casters, they're mostly trophies.<br><br>A naked melee class is virtually useless (monks are an exception).<br><br>A naked caster is 80-90% effective.<br><br>There are only a few items casters actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> need</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (consult www.dictionary.com for the difference between need and want).  Or, let me put it another way, there are very few items that drastically change the effectiveness of a caster.<br><br>I have no problem with the game including spells that are rare, the result of hard quests, REALLY expensive or require a lot of people to get.<br><br>I do have a problem with casters who think they're entitled to spells that drop just because they happen to be the same class as the spell but are quite happy to /random on that blood point.<br><br>Let the flames begin. :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhaagen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haagen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/27/02 10:20:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=550.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Missed one point 55+ spells</span><hr size=1> Malo is one of the things that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   does</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> make or break the Shaman class at 60.  A cleric with group aego is a lot more efficient at buffing a raid than one without. The dropped spells are probably the only things in the game right now that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  do</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> drastically change the effectiveness of a caster.<br><br>For this reason, I agree that they should be expensive, just as high end melee toys are expensive. But I also agree that a character with these spells is more desirable than a character without. The skill of the person behind the character can only get you so far. The right tools are necessary to do the rest of the job. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13524">Margana Malevolent</A><BR>Warlock<BR><A href="http://www.fnurt.net/amici">Amici</A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhaagen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haagen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/27/02 10:26:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/urykarderashken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rykar Derashken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/27/02 11:12:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=550.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Missed one point 55+ spells</span><hr size=1> Malo may break a shaman when they reach 60 but that only applies to shamans who are part of a raiding guild.  A normal pickup group running shaman does not require malo to be able to function, unless they are suicidal and insist on going to places where mobs' resistances are obnoxiously high.<br><br>If you are a shaman who is part of a raiding guild, your guild needs to assist you in attaining your &quot;raid&quot; spells.  And that is what Malo is.  Its a raid spell, not your everyday spell.  Of course camping forever in Emperor wil