d which does not raid often if at all, and generally spends its' time grouping instead, in which case you don't really really need that big spell for your style of play.<br><br>I may have missed this, but is there any super-rare spell which is vital to a class in soloing, raiding, and general grouping scenarios? I can't think of one, but then again I'm a warrior with a small brain. <p>Glork  Gudbasher<BR>55 Troll Warriorioriorior<BR>Keeper of the Troll Brain<BR>Official Pooh Bear Lookalike<BR>Have you eaten a halfling today?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugregar1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gregar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(3/28/02 9:35:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=550.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Missed one point 55+ spells</span><hr size=1> Well, first, Verant only made them rare.  It took players to make them expensive. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But, yes, Verant did not think ahead about economies on older servers.  I haven't seen the community try to alter the madness either.<br><br>Speaking as a Ranger, the few rare drop spells for me will not make or break my effectiveness, so far.  I really do not understand why, in a game named EverQUEST,  all the rare spells don't have alternate quests available to procure them?   Call me weirdo, but questing to get Call of Flame at 50 was very enjoyable for me.<br><br>When I was a young ranger, I used to patiently copy all the cryptic runes on the sides of buildings and towers I saw all over Norrath.  I assumed